               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa gǝnzat “Book of the Funeral Ritual” (fols. 1r-70v, 105v-111v),
                     incomplete&#xD; - Homily by ʾabbā Salāmā, Metropolitan of Ethiopia (fols.
                     21v-25v)&#xD; - Homily by St Jacob of Serug for the funeral of priests and
                     deacons (fols. 40r-46r)&#xD; II) Śǝrʿāta mǝnkʷǝsǝnnā “The Order of the Monastic
                     Profession” (fols. 71r-105v), incomplete.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text II, Śǝrʿāta mǝnkwäsǝnna “The Order of the Monastic Profession”, has
                        similar readings with Grebaut’s edition of ሥርዓተ፡ ምንኵስና፡ ቅድስት (S. GREBAUT,
                        Rituel éthiopien de prise d’habit, Paris 1940) but the order appears
                        completely different. <locus target="#85r">85r</locus> (ጸሎት፡ እምድኅረ፡ አቅነትከ)
                        matches with p. 10 of the edition (ጸሎት፡ ሶበ፡ ያቀንቱ፡ መነኮሳት); <locus
                           target="#85r">85r</locus> matches p. 14 of the edition (ጸሎት፡ ላዕለ፡ ደናግል)
                        .</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
